content.description: This route starts in the crack on the far side of the face. work up to the large ledge. Work through the series of crimps in the little cove (left wall is off). Work over the overhang and straight up.

This route starts on a flake just about directly in the middle of the wall. Work you way up and right to the rounded arete. Next, work straight up through a good line of jugs. Power through the amazing move to the rectangular block and finish the top.  

  This route is some peoples favorite route at High Cliff.

Forgotten Favorite starts in the crack in the middle of the face. Work up and slightly left aiming for the large rectangular block 3/4 of the way up (it's solid). Work further left, then over the roof. Finish the route up by traversing right. 

  This route is a lot of fun with a great flow at the top.

Big Swing Face has been overlooked by many climbers at High Cliff. But it is become much more popular these days. The reason why it attracts most climbers is because it has a quality that most areas at High Cliff lack-- Overhangness (It's not a word, but you know what I mean). This is a great spot to burn out at the end of the day. The majority of the climbs are complete Jug-hauls.
